 this as potentially arising from the production of the\noxygen being more effective at more metal-poor epochs. We also find evidence\nthat for lower mass star's the angular momentum loss in star's with planets as\nmeasured by V sin i is steeper than star's without planets. In general, we find\nthat the fast rotators (V sin i > 5 km/s) are massive stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Nov 2018 08:45:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2018 12:43:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 19 Nov 2018 07:03:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-16"}
